    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ea54ce9f0bdf81c5d1338571a769e8a5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 2931887,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2511915,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2511915/dark-knight",
                "reputation": 8367,
                "display_name": "Dark Knight",
                "accept_rate": 85
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1383405394,
            "creation_date": 1383405394,
            "body": "<p>You need to correct Calendar constants values. Please refer to below code it works fine. <strong>Please remember Month value in calendar starts with 0 and 1 ie, month as 0 means month as Jan<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Calendar c = Calendar.getInstance();\n    c.set(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK,4);\n    c.set(Calendar.WEEK_OF_MONTH,4);\n    c.set(Calendar.MONTH,7);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19743374,
            "question_id": 19743321
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4ec21df1e55febf8deb2e3b24b9cb39b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 195331,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 438154,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/438154/sotirios-delimanolis",
                "reputation": 281049,
                "display_name": "Sotirios Delimanolis",
                "accept_rate": 98
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1383405522,
            "creation_date": 1383405522,
            "body": "<p>The <code>DAY_OF_WEEK<\/code> is Sunday through Saturday. The value 7, indicates <code>SATURDAY<\/code>. The <code>WEEK_OF_MONTH<\/code> is <\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Field number for get and set indicating the week number within the\n  current month. The first week of the month, as defined by\n  getFirstDayOfWeek() and getMinimalDaysInFirstWeek(), has value 1.\n  Subclasses define the value of WEEK_OF_MONTH for days before the first\n  week of the month.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>The <code>MONTH<\/code> numbers start at 0, so <code>10<\/code> is November. You haven't specified a year, so it uses the current year. <\/p>\n\n<p>November's first week Saturday falls on <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Sat Nov 02 11:19:24 EDT 2013\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>What else are you expecting? October? Change your <code>MONTH<\/code> value to <code>9<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 19743401,
            "question_id": 19743321
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e8eb939de5c4bdecd3a8abc734bc2e7f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1887192,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2225572,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2225572/ankit-rustagi",
                "reputation": 5647,
                "display_name": "Ankit Rustagi",
                "accept_rate": 67
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1383405276,
            "creation_date": 1383405276,
            "body": "<p>Try this<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  c.set(2000, 7, 4);  // YYYY M D\n\n  // print the result\n  System.out.println(\"Altered date is :\" + cal.getTime());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19743353,
